> 
> Very brief summary:
> ISO 2022 describes the general setup of character sets,
> ISO 4873 says that the G0 part has to be ASCII,
> ISO 6429 describes the VT100-like escape sequences.
> 
However, although ISO 4873 is a good thing to stick to as much as
possible, we shouldn't limit the console to it.  The DEC VT graphics
set, for example, usually goes in G0.
	-hpa
